children.text: The ceiling insulation batts have been pressed in tight against the underside of the roof, which will allow the expected moisture and condensation that collects on the underside of the roof to transmit across onto the insulation and ceiling linings causing mould and other ill-health effects.
The relevant Australian Standard AS 3999 Thermal Insulation of Dwellings - Bulk Insulation - Installation Requirements states in section 5.3.4.2 that

‘The bulk insulation shall maintain a minimum of 20 mm air gap between the bulk insulation and sarking membranes or underside of the tiles, metal, other roof sheets or battens (see Figure 5.3.4.1.7)’.
The required clearance will need to be installed between the insulation to the underside of the roof to stop the long-term transmission of moisture and condensation across onto the ceiling linings.
